I"X<p>Each request is added to the queue and a loop in the app will process it.</p>

<p>The queue speed is based on the <code class="highlighter-rouge">config.app.loop_speed</code> configuration setting.</p>

<p>Each request is stored and only max_consecutive requests can be made at one time. When testing itâ€™s a good idea to have max_consecutive set to 1 so it will do one request at a time.</p>

<p>The queueing also acts as basic flood protection. If a user is malicious they may try to send hundreds of lines to the bot, or they may copy and paste hundreds of lines by mistake into a client.</p>
